import ¬ęAdic spaces¬Ľ.ValuationSpectrum
import Mathlib.Topology.Compactness.Compact
import Mathlib.Topology.Constructions

/-!
# Compactness of the Valuation Spectrum (scaffolding)

This file begins the port of Huber's proof that `Spv A = ValuationSpectrum A` is a
**quasi-compact** topological space (Wedhorn, Theorem 4.9; Huber, *Continuous valuations*,
1993, Lemma 2.1 / Theorem 3.1).

## High-level strategy

The argument embeds `Spv A` into the function space `(A √ó A) ‚Üí Prop`, equipped with the
product topology (each factor carrying the Sierpinski topology on `Prop`, under which
`{True}` is the only non-trivial open). Tychonoff gives `CompactSpace (A √ó A ‚Üí Prop)`
(the Sierpinski space is compact, and an arbitrary product of compact spaces is compact).
To deduce compactness of `Spv A` one shows:

* `őĻSpv` is a topological embedding (`őĻSpv_isEmbedding`);
* the image of `őĻSpv` inside `(A √ó A ‚Üí Prop)` is a **closed subset** (Phase 2).

A closed subspace of a compact space is compact, giving `CompactSpace (Spv A)`.

## Choice of embedding: basic-open characteristic functions

The most natural-looking embedding would be `v ‚Ü¶ (f, s) ‚Ü¶ v.vle f s` (a direct
characteristic function of the valuative preorder). **However, that embedding does not
induce the right topology on `Spv A`.** The Sierpinski topology has only `{True}` open,
so the sub-basic pullback `{v | v.vle f s}` would be forced to be open in `Spv A` ‚ÄĒ but
this set is *not* open in `Spv A` in general (it fails to be closed under specialisations
that move `s` into the support). The topology on `Spv A` is generated by the strictly
stronger conditions `basicOpen f s = {v | v.vle f s ‚ąß ¬¨ v.vle s 0}`.

The fix is to take the coordinate to be the conjunction directly:

  `őĻSpv v (f, s) := v.vle f s ‚ąß ¬¨ v.vle s 0`,  i.e. `v ‚ąą basicOpen f s`.

With this choice, the Sierpinski sub-basic pullback at coordinate `(f, s)` is exactly
`basicOpen f s`, which is open in `Spv A` by definition of the topology; conversely every
generator of the topology on `Spv A` arises as such a pullback. Hence the product topology
restricts to the given topology on `Spv A` and `őĻSpv` is a topological embedding.

Injectivity still holds: the support information carried by the coordinate `(s, s)`
(specifically, `v ‚ąą basicOpen s s ‚ÜĒ ¬¨ v.vle s 0`) combined with the coordinates `(f, f)`
(telling us when `f ‚ąą supp v`, via `v ‚ąą basicOpen f f ‚ÜĒ ¬¨ v.vle f 0`) is enough to recover
the raw valuative preorder `v.vle f s`.

## Contents of this file (Phase 1 ‚ÄĒ embedding only)

* `ValuationSpectrum.őĻSpv` ‚ÄĒ the Huber embedding (basic-open characteristic form).
* `ValuationSpectrum.őĻSpv_apply` ‚ÄĒ definitional unfolding.
* `ValuationSpectrum.vle_iff_of_őĻSpv` ‚ÄĒ recovers `v.vle f s` from `őĻSpv` values.
* `ValuationSpectrum.őĻSpv_injective` ‚ÄĒ injectivity.
* `ValuationSpectrum.őĻSpv_isInducing` ‚ÄĒ topology agreement.
* `ValuationSpectrum.őĻSpv_isEmbedding` ‚ÄĒ the main embedding theorem.

## Future work (Phase 2 ‚ÄĒ not in this file yet)

* Prove the image of `őĻSpv` is a closed subset of `(A √ó A ‚Üí Prop)`. Concretely, express
  the fact that `r` arises from a valuation in terms of closed conditions in the product
  (each a finite boolean combination of coordinate sub-basics).
* Conclude `CompactSpace (Spv A)` from Tychonoff + closed-subspace compactness + the
  embedding proved here.

## References

* T. Wedhorn, *Adic Spaces*, Theorem 4.9.
* R. Huber, *Continuous valuations*, Math. Z. 212 (1993), 445‚Äď477.
-/

namespace ValuationSpectrum

variable {A : Type*} [CommRing A]

/-! ### The Huber embedding `őĻSpv : Spv A ‚Üí (A √ó A ‚Üí Prop)` -/

/-- **Huber embedding.** Send a point `v ‚ąą Spv A` to the characteristic function of its
basic opens: `(f, s) ‚Ü¶ v ‚ąą basicOpen f s`, unfolded as `v.vle f s ‚ąß ¬¨ v.vle s 0`.

With `Prop` carrying the Sierpinski topology and `A √ó A ‚Üí Prop` the product topology, the
sub-basic open set `{r | r (f, s)}` pulls back to `basicOpen f s`, which is precisely one
of the generating opens of the topology on `Spv A`. Hence the induced topology agrees with
the given topology on `Spv A` (see `őĻSpv_isInducing`). -/
def őĻSpv (v : Spv A) : A √ó A ‚Üí Prop := fun p => v.vle p.1 p.2 ‚ąß ¬¨ v.vle p.2 0

@[simp]
lemma őĻSpv_apply (v : Spv A) (f s : A) :
    őĻSpv v (f, s) = (v.vle f s ‚ąß ¬¨ v.vle s 0) := rfl

/-- The coordinate `(f, s)` of `őĻSpv v` exactly tests membership in `basicOpen f s`. -/
lemma őĻSpv_iff_mem_basicOpen (v : Spv A) (f s : A) :
    őĻSpv v (f, s) ‚ÜĒ v ‚ąą basicOpen f s := Iff.rfl

/-- The coordinate `(s, s)` of `őĻSpv v` tests whether `s` lies outside the support. -/
lemma őĻSpv_diag (v : Spv A) (s : A) : őĻSpv v (s, s) ‚ÜĒ ¬¨ v.vle s 0 := by
  simp [őĻSpv]

/-- The raw valuative preorder `v.vle f s` can be recovered from the `őĻSpv` data.

If `¬¨ v.vle s 0` (i.e. `s ‚ąČ supp v`) then `v.vle f s` is simply the `(f, s)` coordinate.
If `v.vle s 0` (i.e. `s ‚ąą supp v`) then `v.vle f s ‚ÜĒ v.vle f 0`, which can be recovered
from the negations of the `(s, s)` and `(f, f)` coordinates (via `őĻSpv_diag`). -/
lemma vle_iff_őĻSpv (v : Spv A) (f s : A) :
    v.vle f s ‚ÜĒ (őĻSpv v (f, s) ‚ą® (¬¨ őĻSpv v (s, s) ‚ąß ¬¨ őĻSpv v (f, f))) := by
  rw [őĻSpv_diag, őĻSpv_diag]
  simp only [not_not, őĻSpv_apply]
  constructor
  ¬∑ intro h
    by_cases hs : v.vle s 0
    ¬∑ exact Or.inr ‚ü®hs, v.vle_trans h hs‚ü©
    ¬∑ exact Or.inl ‚ü®h, hs‚ü©
  ¬∑ rintro (‚ü®h, _‚ü© | ‚ü®_, hf‚ü©)
    ¬∑ exact h
    ¬∑ exact v.vle_trans hf (v.zero_vle s)

/-- The Huber embedding is injective: two points of `Spv A` with equal basic-open
characteristic functions are equal. -/
lemma őĻSpv_injective : Function.Injective (őĻSpv : Spv A ‚Üí _) := by
  intro v‚āĀ v‚āā h
  apply ValuationSpectrum.ext
  funext f s
  have key : ‚ąÄ f s : A, őĻSpv v‚āĀ (f, s) ‚ÜĒ őĻSpv v‚āā (f, s) := by
    intro f s; exact (congrArg (fun r => r (f, s)) h).to_iff
  exact propext <| by
    rw [vle_iff_őĻSpv, vle_iff_őĻSpv]
    simp only [key]

/-! ### `őĻSpv` is a topological embedding -/

/-- The topology on `Spv A` coincides with the topology induced from the product topology
on `(A √ó A ‚Üí Prop)` (product of Sierpinski). -/
lemma őĻSpv_isInducing : Topology.IsInducing (őĻSpv : Spv A ‚Üí (A √ó A ‚Üí Prop)) := by
  refine ‚ü®?_‚ü©
  -- Unfold Pi topology to an iInf of single-coordinate induced topologies.
  rw [show (Pi.topologicalSpace :
      TopologicalSpace (A √ó A ‚Üí Prop)) = ‚®Ö p, TopologicalSpace.induced
        (fun r : A √ó A ‚Üí Prop => r p) sierpinskiSpace from rfl]
  rw [induced_iInf]
  -- Each coordinate's pullback of the Sierpinski generator is a basic open.
  have hcoord : ‚ąÄ p : A √ó A,
      TopologicalSpace.induced ((fun r : A √ó A ‚Üí Prop => r p) ‚ąė őĻSpv) sierpinskiSpace =
        TopologicalSpace.generateFrom {basicOpen p.1 p.2} := by
    intro p
    rw [show sierpinskiSpace = TopologicalSpace.generateFrom {{True}} from rfl,
        induced_generateFrom_eq]
    congr 1
    ext s
    refine ‚ü®?_, ?_‚ü©
    ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®t, ht, rfl‚ü©
      rw [Set.mem_singleton_iff] at ht
      subst ht
      refine Set.mem_singleton_iff.mpr ?_
      ext v
      simp [Function.comp, őĻSpv, basicOpen]
    ¬∑ rintro hs
      rw [Set.mem_singleton_iff] at hs
      refine ‚ü®{True}, Set.mem_singleton _, ?_‚ü©
      subst hs
      ext v
      simp [Function.comp, őĻSpv, basicOpen]
  simp_rw [induced_compose, hcoord]
  -- Match the iInf of single-generator topologies to the Spv topology.
  rw [show (‚®Ö p : A √ó A, TopologicalSpace.generateFrom {basicOpen p.1 p.2}) =
      TopologicalSpace.generateFrom (‚čÉ p : A √ó A, {basicOpen p.1 p.2}) from
      generateFrom_iUnion.symm]
  unfold ValuationSpectrum.instTopologicalSpace
  congr 1
  ext U
  simp only [Set.mem_iUnion, Set.mem_singleton_iff, Set.mem_setOf_eq, Prod.exists]

/-- **Huber embedding ‚ÄĒ Phase 1 main result.** The map `őĻSpv : Spv A ‚Üí (A √ó A ‚Üí Prop)`
is a topological embedding (injective + induced topology agrees).

This is the content of the topological half of Wedhorn's Theorem 4.9 / Huber 1993, Lemma
2.1. The compactness conclusion additionally requires closedness of the image, which is
deferred to Phase 2. -/
theorem őĻSpv_isEmbedding : Topology.IsEmbedding (őĻSpv : Spv A ‚Üí (A √ó A ‚Üí Prop)) where
  eq_induced := őĻSpv_isInducing.eq_induced
  injective := őĻSpv_injective

/-- **Sierpinski `Prop` is T0.** Two points `True` and `False` are
distinguished by the open set `{True}`. -/
instance : T0Space Prop := by
  refine ‚ü®fun p q hpq ‚Ü¶ ?_‚ü©
  have hopen : IsOpen ({True} : Set Prop) :=
    TopologicalSpace.GenerateOpen.basic _ (Set.mem_singleton _)
  have hiff : p ‚ąą ({True} : Set Prop) ‚ÜĒ q ‚ąą ({True} : Set Prop) := hpq.mem_open_iff hopen
  -- p ‚ąą {True} iff p = True iff p (since p : Prop).
  simp only [Set.mem_singleton_iff, eq_iff_iff, iff_true] at hiff
  exact propext hiff

/-- **`Spv A` is T0.** Inherited from the Huber embedding into the
T0 product `(A √ó A ‚Üí Prop)`. -/
instance : T0Space (Spv A) := őĻSpv_isEmbedding.t0Space

/-- **`{True}` is dense in Sierpinski `Prop`.** Equivalently `closure {True} = Set.univ`. -/
lemma dense_true : Dense ({True} : Set Prop) := by
  intro p
  rw [mem_closure_iff]
  intro U hU hpU
  refine ‚ü®True, ?_, Set.mem_singleton _‚ü©
  -- True ‚ąą U: induct on open structure.
  induction hU with
  | basic s hs =>
    rw [show s = {True} from (Set.mem_singleton_iff.mp hs)]
    exact Set.mem_singleton _
  | univ => trivial
  | inter U‚āĀ U‚āā _ _ ih‚āĀ ih‚āā =>
    exact ‚ü®ih‚āĀ hpU.1, ih‚āā hpU.2‚ü©
  | sUnion S _ ih =>
    obtain ‚ü®s, hsS, hps‚ü© := hpU
    exact ‚ü®s, hsS, ih s hsS hps‚ü©

/-- **Sierpinski `Prop` is QuasiSober.** -/
instance : QuasiSober Prop where
  sober {S} hirr hclosed := by
    by_cases hT : (True : Prop) ‚ąą S
    ¬∑ -- True ‚ąą S ‚Üí S ‚äá closure({True}) = Set.univ.
      refine ‚ü®True, ?_‚ü©
      have hsub : closure ({True} : Set Prop) ‚äÜ S :=
        hclosed.closure_subset_iff.mpr (Set.singleton_subset_iff.mpr hT)
      have hSuniv : S = Set.univ :=
        Set.eq_univ_of_univ_subset (dense_true.closure_eq ‚Ėł hsub)
      rw [hSuniv]
      exact dense_true.closure_eq
    ¬∑ -- True ‚ąČ S, S nonempty + closed ‚Üí S ‚äÜ {False} (since p ‚ąą S ‚Üí p ‚Č† True).
      refine ‚ü®False, ?_‚ü©
      have hSsub : S ‚äÜ {False} := by
        intro p hp
        rw [Set.mem_singleton_iff, eq_iff_iff, iff_false]
        intro hpT
        exact hT (eq_true hpT ‚Ėł hp)
      obtain ‚ü®p, hp‚ü© := hirr.nonempty
      have hFmem : False ‚ąą S := by
        have : p = False := Set.mem_singleton_iff.mp (hSsub hp)
        exact this ‚Ėł hp
      have hSeq : S = {False} :=
        Set.eq_singleton_iff_unique_mem.mpr ‚ü®hFmem, fun q hq ‚Ü¶ Set.mem_singleton_iff.mp (hSsub hq)‚ü©
      rw [hSeq]
      apply IsClosed.closure_eq
      -- {False} = {True}Š∂ú in Prop, and {True} is open.
      have hcompl : ({False} : Set Prop) = ({True} : Set Prop)Š∂ú := by
        ext q; simp [Set.mem_singleton_iff, eq_iff_iff]
      rw [hcompl, isClosed_compl_iff]
      exact TopologicalSpace.GenerateOpen.basic _ (Set.mem_singleton _)



/-! ### Characterising the image of `őĻSpv`

We now capture the **set-theoretic** image of `őĻSpv` via a predicate `IsValuationChar`.
An `r : A √ó A ‚Üí Prop` lies in the range of `őĻSpv` iff:

* a *recovered* preorder `vleOf r` (built from `vle_iff_őĻSpv`) satisfies all six
  `ValuativeRel` axioms, and
* `r` itself is the basic-open indicator of that preorder:
  `r (f, s) ‚ÜĒ vleOf r f s ‚ąß ¬¨ vleOf r s 0`.

The first family of conditions alone is not enough to force `r = őĻSpv v` for the
associated `v`: we also need to know that `r` is the characteristic function of *that*
preorder's basic opens rather than some unrelated function. The extra `apply_iff`
field in `IsValuationChar` records that round-trip condition, and as we shall see it is
automatic for any `r = őĻSpv v`.

The **topological** part ‚ÄĒ showing `{r | IsValuationChar r}` is closed in the product
Sierpinski topology ‚ÄĒ is still deferred to a later phase (see the TODO block at the end
of this file). -/

/-- The preorder on `A` recovered from a characteristic function `r : A √ó A ‚Üí Prop`,
matching `vle_iff_őĻSpv`: `v.vle f s ‚ÜĒ r (f, s) ‚ą® (¬¨ r (s, s) ‚ąß ¬¨ r (f, f))`. -/
def vleOf (r : A √ó A ‚Üí Prop) (f s : A) : Prop :=
  r (f, s) ‚ą® (¬¨ r (s, s) ‚ąß ¬¨ r (f, f))

lemma vleOf_őĻSpv (v : Spv A) (f s : A) : vleOf (őĻSpv v) f s ‚ÜĒ v.vle f s :=
  (vle_iff_őĻSpv v f s).symm

/-- A characteristic function `r : A √ó A ‚Üí Prop` is a **valuation characteristic**
iff:

* the recovered preorder `vleOf r` satisfies the six `ValuativeRel` axioms
  (total, transitive, additive, left-multiplicative, cancellative, and `¬¨ 1 ‚Č§ 0`);
* `r` is the basic-open indicator of that preorder ‚ÄĒ i.e.
  `r (f, s) ‚ÜĒ vleOf r f s ‚ąß ¬¨ vleOf r s 0` for every `(f, s)`.

By `vle_iff_őĻSpv` every `őĻSpv v` is a valuation characteristic, and conversely every
valuation characteristic comes from a unique `v : Spv A` (see
`őĻSpv_mem_isValuationChar` and `exists_spv_of_isValuationChar`). -/
structure IsValuationChar (r : A √ó A ‚Üí Prop) : Prop where
  /-- Totality: `vleOf r f s ‚ą® vleOf r s f`. -/
  vle_total : ‚ąÄ f s : A, vleOf r f s ‚ą® vleOf r s f
  /-- Transitivity of the recovered preorder. -/
  vle_trans : ‚ąÄ {x y z : A}, vleOf r x y ‚Üí vleOf r y z ‚Üí vleOf r x z
  /-- Additivity: `vleOf r x z ‚Üí vleOf r y z ‚Üí vleOf r (x + y) z`. -/
  vle_add : ‚ąÄ {x y z : A}, vleOf r x z ‚Üí vleOf r y z ‚Üí vleOf r (x + y) z
  /-- Left multiplication by a constant preserves the preorder. -/
  mul_vle_mul_left : ‚ąÄ {x y : A} (_ : vleOf r x y) (z : A), vleOf r (x * z) (y * z)
  /-- Cancellation: a non-zero factor can be removed from both sides. -/
  vle_mul_cancel : ‚ąÄ {x y z : A}, ¬¨ vleOf r z 0 ‚Üí vleOf r (x * z) (y * z) ‚Üí vleOf r x y
  /-- Non-triviality: `1` is not `‚Č§ 0`. -/
  not_vle_one_zero : ¬¨ vleOf r 1 0
  /-- Consistency: `r` is the basic-open indicator of the recovered preorder. -/
  apply_iff : ‚ąÄ f s : A, r (f, s) ‚ÜĒ vleOf r f s ‚ąß ¬¨ vleOf r s 0

/-- Every point `v : Spv A` gives a valuation characteristic `őĻSpv v`. -/
lemma őĻSpv_mem_isValuationChar (v : Spv A) : IsValuationChar (őĻSpv v) := by
  refine
    { vle_total := ?_, vle_trans := ?_, vle_add := ?_,
      mul_vle_mul_left := ?_, vle_mul_cancel := ?_, not_vle_one_zero := ?_,
      apply_iff := ?_ }
  ¬∑ intro f s
    rcases v.vle_total f s with h | h
    ¬∑ exact Or.inl ((vleOf_őĻSpv v f s).mpr h)
    ¬∑ exact Or.inr ((vleOf_őĻSpv v s f).mpr h)
  ¬∑ intro x y z hxy hyz
    exact (vleOf_őĻSpv v x z).mpr
      (v.vle_trans ((vleOf_őĻSpv v x y).mp hxy) ((vleOf_őĻSpv v y z).mp hyz))
  ¬∑ intro x y z hxz hyz
    exact (vleOf_őĻSpv v _ _).mpr
      (v.vle_add ((vleOf_őĻSpv v x z).mp hxz) ((vleOf_őĻSpv v y z).mp hyz))
  ¬∑ intro x y hxy z
    exact (vleOf_őĻSpv v _ _).mpr
      (v.mul_vle_mul_left ((vleOf_őĻSpv v x y).mp hxy) z)
  ¬∑ intro x y z hz h
    refine (vleOf_őĻSpv v x y).mpr (v.vle_mul_cancel ?_ ((vleOf_őĻSpv v _ _).mp h))
    intro hz0
    exact hz ((vleOf_őĻSpv v z 0).mpr hz0)
  ¬∑ intro h
    exact v.not_vle_one_zero ((vleOf_őĻSpv v 1 0).mp h)
  ¬∑ intro f s
    constructor
    ¬∑ intro h
      refine ‚ü®(vleOf_őĻSpv v f s).mpr h.1, ?_‚ü©
      intro hs
      exact h.2 ((vleOf_őĻSpv v s 0).mp hs)
    ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®hfs, hs0‚ü©
      exact ‚ü®(vleOf_őĻSpv v f s).mp hfs, fun hs ‚Ü¶ hs0 ((vleOf_őĻSpv v s 0).mpr hs)‚ü©

/-- A valuation characteristic `r` determines a `ValuativeRel` on `A` with `vle = vleOf r`.

This packages the six axioms carried by `IsValuationChar r` as a `ValuativeRel` record,
so that the `Spv A` whose underlying relation is `vleOf r` can be formed. -/
@[implicit_reducible]
def IsValuationChar.toValuativeRel {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Prop} (hr : IsValuationChar r) :
    ValuativeRel A where
  vle f s := vleOf r f s
  vle_total := hr.vle_total
  vle_trans := hr.vle_trans
  vle_add := hr.vle_add
  mul_vle_mul_left := hr.mul_vle_mul_left
  vle_mul_comm := by intro x y; rw [mul_comm]; exact (hr.vle_total _ _).elim id id
  vle_mul_cancel := hr.vle_mul_cancel
  not_vle_one_zero := hr.not_vle_one_zero

/-- The `Spv A` point associated to a valuation characteristic `r`. -/
def IsValuationChar.toSpv {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Prop} (hr : IsValuationChar r) : Spv A :=
  ‚ü®hr.toValuativeRel‚ü©

@[simp] lemma IsValuationChar.toSpv_vle {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Prop} (hr : IsValuationChar r)
    (f s : A) : hr.toSpv.vle f s ‚ÜĒ vleOf r f s := Iff.rfl

/-- **Valuation-characteristic inverse to `őĻSpv`.** Every valuation characteristic is in
the image of `őĻSpv`: from `hr : IsValuationChar r`, the point `hr.toSpv` satisfies
`őĻSpv hr.toSpv = r`. -/
lemma őĻSpv_toSpv {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Prop} (hr : IsValuationChar r) :
    őĻSpv hr.toSpv = r := by
  funext p
  obtain ‚ü®f, s‚ü© := p
  change (hr.toSpv.vle f s ‚ąß ¬¨ hr.toSpv.vle s 0) = r (f, s)
  rw [hr.toSpv_vle, hr.toSpv_vle]
  exact propext (hr.apply_iff f s).symm

/-- Existence form of the inverse: every `r` with `IsValuationChar r` lies in the range
of `őĻSpv`. -/
lemma exists_spv_of_isValuationChar {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Prop} (hr : IsValuationChar r) :
    ‚ąÉ v : Spv A, őĻSpv v = r :=
  ‚ü®hr.toSpv, őĻSpv_toSpv hr‚ü©

/-- **Main characterisation of the range of `őĻSpv`.** An `r : A √ó A ‚Üí Prop` is in the
range of `őĻSpv` iff it is a valuation characteristic. -/
theorem isValuationChar_iff_mem_range (r : A √ó A ‚Üí Prop) :
    IsValuationChar r ‚ÜĒ ‚ąÉ v : Spv A, őĻSpv v = r :=
  ‚ü®exists_spv_of_isValuationChar, fun ‚ü®v, hv‚ü© ‚Ü¶ hv ‚Ėł őĻSpv_mem_isValuationChar v‚ü©

/-- The image of `őĻSpv` as a set equals the set of valuation characteristics. -/
theorem range_őĻSpv :
    Set.range (őĻSpv : Spv A ‚Üí (A √ó A ‚Üí Prop)) = {r | IsValuationChar r} := by
  ext r
  simp only [Set.mem_range, Set.mem_setOf_eq]
  exact (isValuationChar_iff_mem_range r).symm

/-! ### Sierpinski coordinate sub-basics

Each coordinate evaluation `r ‚Ü¶ r p : (A √ó A ‚Üí Prop) ‚Üí Prop` is continuous (it is a
projection in a product topology). Combined with the Sierpinski facts that `{True}` is
open and `{False}` is closed, this yields two basic topological facts about the product:

* `{r | r p}` is **open** (sub-basis of the product Sierpinski topology),
* `{r | ¬¨ r p}` is **closed** (its complement is the open set above).

These are the only "building blocks" of the product topology (and its closed sets); see
the asymmetry note at the end of this file. -/

omit [CommRing A] in
/-- The coordinate-evaluation set `{r | r p}` is open in the Sierpinski product. -/
lemma isOpen_setOf_apply (p : A √ó A) :
    IsOpen {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Prop | r p} :=
  continuous_Prop.mp (continuous_apply p)

omit [CommRing A] in
/-- The coordinate-negation set `{r | ¬¨ r p}` is closed in the Sierpinski product. -/
lemma isClosed_setOf_not_apply (p : A √ó A) :
    IsClosed {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Prop | ¬¨ r p} :=
  (isOpen_setOf_apply p).isClosed_compl

/-! ### Compactness of the product space

`Prop` is finite and hence compact in every topology (in particular the Sierpinski
topology `sierpinskiSpace`). Tychonoff (`Pi.compactSpace`) then gives compactness of the
full function space. This is the target compact ambient space for the Huber embedding. -/

/-- `Prop` with its Sierpinski topology is compact (indeed, `Prop` is finite). -/
instance : CompactSpace Prop := Finite.compactSpace

/-- **Tychonoff for the Huber ambient space.** The product `A √ó A ‚Üí Prop`, with each
factor in the Sierpinski topology, is compact. -/
instance : CompactSpace (A √ó A ‚Üí Prop) := Pi.compactSpace

/-! ### Phase 2: Sierpinski closedness fails; pivot to Alexander sub-basis

The naive Phase 2 plan ‚ÄĒ "show `IsClosed {r | IsValuationChar r}` in the product
Sierpinski topology, then conclude `CompactSpace (Spv A)` via `range_őĻSpv`,
`őĻSpv_isEmbedding`, and closed-subspace-of-compact-is-compact" ‚ÄĒ **does not succeed in
this topology**. The obstruction is intrinsic to the Sierpinski choice and not a matter
of proof engineering; we record the counterexample briefly below, then turn to the
correct route (Alexander's sub-basis theorem, `compactSpace_generateFrom`).

#### Why the Sierpinski range is generally *not* closed

Sierpinski declares `{True}` open but not closed; the closed sub-basic sets in the
product are exactly of the form `{r | ¬¨ r p}`. A basic Sierpinski neighbourhood of a
point `r‚āÄ` is determined by the *True*-coordinates of `r‚āÄ` and can never forbid "True"
at further coordinates. Taking `s ‚ąą A` not nilpotent and `r‚āÄ p := (p = (s, s))` one
checks `r‚āÄ` is not a valuation characteristic (e.g. `vle_total` fails at `(f, s)` for
most `f`), yet every Sierpinski neighbourhood of `r‚āÄ` meets `Set.range őĻSpv` (via a
valuation `v` with `s ‚ąČ supp v`). Hence the range is *not* closed in the Sierpinski
product. The same pathology means `vle_total` itself is not pointwise closed in this
topology.

#### The Alexander route

Mathlib's `compactSpace_generateFrom` (a.k.a. **Alexander's subbasis theorem**, in
`Mathlib.Topology.Compactness.Compact`) states that a topological space is compact
whenever every cover by elements of a chosen subbasis admits a finite subcover. The
`Spv A` topology is defined exactly as `generateFrom {U | ‚ąÉ f s, U = basicOpen f s}`
(see `ValuationSpectrum.instTopologicalSpace`), so Alexander applies directly, with
**no need for any embedding or closed-subspace argument**. This avoids the Sierpinski
obstruction outlined above and gives the cleanest path to `CompactSpace (Spv A)`.

We set up the Alexander API below: we expose a reusable reformulation
`compactSpace_iff_subbasic_subcover` that converts `CompactSpace (Spv A)` into the
concrete finite-subcover condition on families `(f_i, s_i)`. The **verification** of
that condition is the genuine Huber content (Wedhorn Thm 4.9 / Huber 1993) and is
still left open: the standard proof runs a Zorn / ultrafilter argument on pairs
`(valuation, prime)`, which is sizeable valuation-theoretic work. -/

/-! ### Alexander sub-basis reformulation of Spv compactness -/

/-- Membership in the Spv sub-basis: `U` is a sub-basic open iff `U = basicOpen f s`
for some `f s : A`. This is a restatement of the defining set of
`ValuationSpectrum.instTopologicalSpace`. -/
def IsSubbasicOpen (U : Set (Spv A)) : Prop := ‚ąÉ f s : A, U = basicOpen f s

/-- The Spv topology is `generateFrom` the set of sub-basic opens. Unfolds the
definition of `instTopologicalSpace`. -/
lemma instTopologicalSpace_eq_generateFrom :
    (instTopologicalSpace : TopologicalSpace (Spv A)) =
      TopologicalSpace.generateFrom {U | IsSubbasicOpen U} := rfl

/-- **Alexander sub-basis theorem, applied to `Spv A`.** If every cover of `Spv A`
by sub-basic opens (basic opens `basicOpen f s`) admits a finite subcover, then
`Spv A` is compact.

This is the direct content of Wedhorn Theorem 4.9 / Huber, *Continuous valuations*
(1993), reformulated purely as a statement about covers of the underlying type by
basic opens. -/
theorem compactSpace_of_subbasic_subcover
    (h : ‚ąÄ P ‚äÜ {U : Set (Spv A) | IsSubbasicOpen U}, ‚čÉ‚āÄ P = Set.univ ‚Üí
      ‚ąÉ Q ‚äÜ P, Q.Finite ‚ąß ‚čÉ‚āÄ Q = Set.univ) :
    CompactSpace (Spv A) :=
  compactSpace_generateFrom instTopologicalSpace_eq_generateFrom h

/-- **Converse direction.** If `Spv A` is compact, then every cover of `Spv A` by
sub-basic opens admits a finite subcover. (Trivial direction: every sub-basic open is
open, so this is just `IsCompact.elim_finite_subcover_image`.) -/
theorem subbasic_subcover_of_compactSpace [CompactSpace (Spv A)]
    (P : Set (Set (Spv A))) (hP : P ‚äÜ {U : Set (Spv A) | IsSubbasicOpen U})
    (hcov : ‚čÉ‚āÄ P = Set.univ) :
    ‚ąÉ Q ‚äÜ P, Q.Finite ‚ąß ‚čÉ‚āÄ Q = Set.univ := by
  have hopen : ‚ąÄ U ‚ąą P, IsOpen U := by
    intro U hU
    obtain ‚ü®f, s, rfl‚ü© := hP hU
    exact TopologicalSpace.isOpen_generateFrom_of_mem ‚ü®f, s, rfl‚ü©
  have hcompact : IsCompact (Set.univ : Set (Spv A)) := isCompact_univ
  obtain ‚ü®Q, hQP, hQfin, hQcov‚ü© :=
    hcompact.elim_finite_subcover_image hopen (by simpa [Set.sUnion_eq_biUnion] using hcov.ge)
  refine ‚ü®Q, hQP, hQfin, ?_‚ü©
  apply Set.eq_univ_of_univ_subset
  simpa [Set.sUnion_eq_biUnion] using hQcov

/-- **Alexander reformulation.** `Spv A` is compact **iff** every cover by sub-basic
opens admits a finite subcover. This reduces the compactness question for the
valuation spectrum to a purely combinatorial statement about families of basic
opens. -/
theorem compactSpace_iff_subbasic_subcover :
    CompactSpace (Spv A) ‚ÜĒ ‚ąÄ P ‚äÜ {U : Set (Spv A) | IsSubbasicOpen U},
      ‚čÉ‚āÄ P = Set.univ ‚Üí ‚ąÉ Q ‚äÜ P, Q.Finite ‚ąß ‚čÉ‚āÄ Q = Set.univ :=
  ‚ü®fun _ => subbasic_subcover_of_compactSpace,
    fun h => compactSpace_of_subbasic_subcover h‚ü©


/-! ### Status of `CompactSpace (Spv A)`

`compactSpace_of_subbasic_subcover` (and the equivalent
`compactSpace_iff_subbasic_subcover`) reduces the compactness of `Spv A` to a
finite-subcover property for families of basic opens. Mathematically, the
statement we still need is:

  `‚ąÄ P ‚äÜ {basicOpen f s | f s : A}, ‚čÉ‚āÄ P = univ ‚Üí ‚ąÉ Q ‚äÜ P finite, ‚čÉ‚āÄ Q = univ`.

Standard proofs (Huber 1993 Lemma 2.1; Wedhorn, *Adic Spaces*, proof of Thm 4.9) go
via an ultrafilter / Zorn argument on pairs `(valuation, prime)`: assuming no finite
subcover, one picks an ultrafilter on the failures, extracts a compatible
`(valuation ring, prime ideal)` configuration, and shows the resulting `v ‚ąą Spv A`
is not in any `basicOpen (f i) (s i)`, contradicting the hypothesised cover. This
requires substantial valuation-ring infrastructure (existence of valuation rings
dominating a local ring, Chevalley-style extension lemmas). It is out of scope for
the present file.

Alternative routes that do not depend on this extension theory:

* Realise `Spv A` as a spectral space via `PrimeSpectrum.compactSpace` of an auxiliary
  ring (Huber's 1993 construction via the valuation ring of the generic fibre). This
  is conceptually cleaner but needs the full `őď`-valuation equivalence.

* Embed into a discrete power `(A √ó A ‚Üí Bool)` (compact by Tychonoff + `Finite Bool`)
  with the image characterised as a closed subset by clopen cylinder conditions for
  each `ValuativeRel` axiom, then transfer compactness through `őĻSpv_isEmbedding`.
  This route is scaffolded below (`őĻSpv_bool`, `boolToProp`, and the factorisation
  `őĻSpv_eq_boolToProp_comp_őĻSpv_bool`) so that the remaining obligation is exactly
  `IsClosed (Set.range őĻSpv_bool)` ‚ÄĒ an intersection of ‚Č§ 7 closed cylinder
  families, one per `IsValuationChar` field. Completing this step would yield
  `CompactSpace (Spv A)` via `őĻSpv_isEmbedding.isCompact_iff`.

The ambient compactness instances and the Sierpinski embedding
(`őĻSpv_isEmbedding`, `range_őĻSpv`) remain useful for either route, and the
Alexander reformulation provided here is the cleanest interface for the
ultrafilter-style proof. -/

/-! ### Scaffolding for the Bool / discrete-product route

We expose the Bool-valued version of the Huber embedding,

  `őĻSpv_bool : Spv A ‚Üí (A √ó A ‚Üí Bool)`,  `v ‚Ü¶ fun p => decide (v ‚ąą basicOpen p.1 p.2)`,

together with the coordinate-wise conversion `boolToProp : Bool ‚Üí Prop`, so that
`őĻSpv = boolToProp ‚ąė őĻSpv_bool`. The target space `(A √ó A ‚Üí Bool)` carries the
product of the discrete topology on `Bool`; it is compact by Tychonoff and `Finite
Bool`. Finishing the compactness proof reduces to showing `IsClosed (Set.range
őĻSpv_bool)` in this discrete product ‚ÄĒ a closed-cylinder argument on the
`IsValuationChar` axioms. -/

/-- **Bool-valued Huber embedding.** Encodes `v ‚ąą basicOpen p.1 p.2` as a Bool. -/
noncomputable def őĻSpv_bool (v : Spv A) : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool := fun p =>
  @decide (v.vle p.1 p.2 ‚ąß ¬¨ v.vle p.2 0) (Classical.dec _)

-- (We state the decidability explicitly via `Classical.dec` rather than relying on
-- the `open Classical` diamond, since the underlying `ValuativeRel.vle` has no
-- automatic `Decidable` instance.)

@[simp]
lemma őĻSpv_bool_apply (v : Spv A) (f s : A) :
    őĻSpv_bool v (f, s) = (@decide _ (Classical.dec (v.vle f s ‚ąß ¬¨ v.vle s 0))) := rfl

/-- Pointwise conversion `Bool ‚Üí Prop`: `true ‚Ü¶ True`, `false ‚Ü¶ False` (via equality).
-/
def boolToProp (b : Bool) : Prop := b = true

omit [CommRing A] in
@[simp]
lemma boolToProp_decide {p : Prop} (hp : Decidable p) : boolToProp (decide p) ‚ÜĒ p :=
  decide_eq_true_iff

/-- **Factorisation:** `őĻSpv = (boolToProp ‚ąė ¬∑) ‚ąė őĻSpv_bool`. In particular, the
Sierpinski-valued embedding is the continuous image of the Bool-valued one under
the coordinate-wise `boolToProp` map. -/
lemma őĻSpv_eq_boolToProp_comp_őĻSpv_bool (v : Spv A) :
    őĻSpv v = fun p => boolToProp (őĻSpv_bool v p) := by
  funext p
  simp only [őĻSpv, őĻSpv_bool, boolToProp]
  exact propext (@decide_eq_true_iff _ (Classical.dec _)).symm

/-- `őĻSpv_bool` is injective. Follows from `őĻSpv_injective` via the factorisation,
since `boolToProp` is injective on `Bool`. -/
lemma őĻSpv_bool_injective : Function.Injective (őĻSpv_bool : Spv A ‚Üí _) := by
  intro v‚āĀ v‚āā h
  apply őĻSpv_injective
  rw [őĻSpv_eq_boolToProp_comp_őĻSpv_bool, őĻSpv_eq_boolToProp_comp_őĻSpv_bool, h]

/-- `Bool` is compact in its discrete topology (it is finite). -/
example : CompactSpace Bool := Finite.compactSpace

/-- **Tychonoff, Bool version.** The product `A √ó A ‚Üí Bool` with discrete factors is
compact. Together with `Finite.compactSpace` and `DiscreteTopology Bool` this gives
a Cantor-style compactum as ambient space for the Bool Huber embedding. -/
instance : CompactSpace (A √ó A ‚Üí Bool) := Pi.compactSpace

omit [CommRing A] in
/-- The coordinate-wise `boolToProp` map
`(A √ó A ‚Üí Bool) ‚Üí (A √ó A ‚Üí Prop)` is continuous. Each coordinate reduces to the map
`b ‚Ü¶ (b = true) : Bool ‚Üí Prop` with Sierpinski codomain, which pulls back `{True}` to
`{true}` ‚ÄĒ open in discrete `Bool`. -/
lemma continuous_boolToProp_pi :
    Continuous (fun r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool => (fun p => boolToProp (r p)) : _ ‚Üí (A √ó A ‚Üí Prop)) := by
  refine continuous_pi fun p => ?_
  -- `fun r => boolToProp (r p) = ((r p = true))` is the composition of `r ‚Ü¶ r p`
  -- (continuous, `continuous_apply`) with `b ‚Ü¶ b = true : Bool ‚Üí Prop` (continuous
  -- since `Bool` is discrete).
  have h1 : Continuous (fun r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool => r p) := continuous_apply p
  have h2 : Continuous (fun b : Bool => boolToProp b) := by
    exact continuous_of_discreteTopology
  exact h2.comp h1

/-! ### Closedness of `range őĻSpv_bool` in the discrete Bool product

We now carry out the closed-cylinder argument: each `IsValuationChar` axiom,
evaluated at `fun p => r p = true` for `r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool`, is an intersection of
clopen cylinder sets in `(A √ó A ‚Üí Bool)` (with the discrete product topology).
The arbitrary intersection of clopens is closed, so `range őĻSpv_bool` is closed.

Combined with the ambient `CompactSpace (A √ó A ‚Üí Bool)` and the factorisation
`őĻSpv = (boolToProp ‚ąė ¬∑) ‚ąė őĻSpv_bool` plus continuity of the coordinate-wise
`boolToProp` map, this gives `IsCompact (range őĻSpv)`, which via
`őĻSpv_isEmbedding.isCompact_iff Set.univ` yields `CompactSpace (Spv A)`. -/

/-- The **Bool-valued recovered preorder** on `A` associated to `r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool`.
This is the pointwise Bool image of `vleOf (fun p ‚Ü¶ r p = true)`; see
`vleOfBool_iff_vleOf_decide` below. -/
def vleOfBool (r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool) (f s : A) : Prop :=
  r (f, s) = true ‚ą® (r (s, s) = false ‚ąß r (f, f) = false)

omit [CommRing A] in
lemma vleOfBool_iff_vleOf_decide (r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool) (f s : A) :
    vleOfBool r f s ‚ÜĒ vleOf (fun p => r p = true) f s := by
  simp only [vleOfBool, vleOf, Bool.not_eq_true]

/-- A `r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool` is a **Bool valuation characteristic** iff the Prop-valued
function `fun p => r p = true` is a valuation characteristic in the sense of
`IsValuationChar`. -/
def IsValuationCharBool (r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool) : Prop :=
  IsValuationChar (fun p => r p = true)

omit [CommRing A] in
/-- Coordinate-at-a-point evaluation is continuous on `A √ó A ‚Üí Bool`. -/
lemma continuous_coord_bool (p : A √ó A) :
    Continuous (fun r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool => r p) := continuous_apply p

omit [CommRing A] in
/-- Every singleton in the discrete `Bool` is open; hence `{r | r p = b}` is
open in the discrete product. -/
lemma isOpen_coord_eq (p : A √ó A) (b : Bool) :
    IsOpen {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | r p = b} :=
  (continuous_coord_bool p).isOpen_preimage {b} (isOpen_discrete {b})

omit [CommRing A] in
/-- The set `{r | r p = b}` is **closed** in the discrete product. -/
lemma isClosed_coord_eq (p : A √ó A) (b : Bool) :
    IsClosed {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | r p = b} :=
  (isClosed_discrete {b}).preimage (continuous_coord_bool p)

omit [CommRing A] in
/-- The set `{r | r (f,s) = true}` is closed (and open) in the discrete product. -/
lemma isClosed_coord_true (p : A √ó A) :
    IsClosed {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | r p = true} := isClosed_coord_eq p true

omit [CommRing A] in
/-- The set `{r | r (f,s) = false}` is closed (and open) in the discrete product. -/
lemma isClosed_coord_false (p : A √ó A) :
    IsClosed {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | r p = false} := isClosed_coord_eq p false

/-! #### Closedness of the individual `IsValuationChar` axioms (Bool form) -/

omit [CommRing A] in
/-- The set `{r | vleOfBool r f s}` is closed in the discrete product. -/
lemma isClosed_vleOfBool (f s : A) :
    IsClosed {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | vleOfBool r f s} := by
  -- vleOfBool r f s = r (f,s) = true ‚ą® (r (s,s) = false ‚ąß r (f,f) = false)
  have h1 : IsClosed {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | r (f, s) = true} := isClosed_coord_true (f, s)
  have h2 : IsClosed {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | r (s, s) = false} := isClosed_coord_false (s, s)
  have h3 : IsClosed {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | r (f, f) = false} := isClosed_coord_false (f, f)
  -- The target set is h1 ‚ą™ (h2 ‚ą© h3).
  have : {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | vleOfBool r f s} =
      {r | r (f, s) = true} ‚ą™ ({r | r (s, s) = false} ‚ą© {r | r (f, f) = false}) := by
    ext r; simp [vleOfBool]
  rw [this]; exact h1.union (h2.inter h3)

omit [CommRing A] in
/-- The set `{r | ¬¨ vleOfBool r u v}` is closed in the discrete product. -/
lemma isClosed_not_vleOfBool (u v : A) :
    IsClosed {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | ¬¨ vleOfBool r u v} := by
  -- ¬¨ vleOfBool r u v = (r (u,v) = false) ‚ąß (r (v,v) = true ‚ą® r (u,u) = true)
  have : {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | ¬¨ vleOfBool r u v} =
      {r | r (u, v) = false} ‚ą©
        ({r | r (v, v) = true} ‚ą™ {r | r (u, u) = true}) := by
    ext r
    constructor
    ¬∑ intro h
      simp only [vleOfBool, not_or, not_and_or, Bool.not_eq_true, Bool.not_eq_false] at h
      refine ‚ü®h.1, ?_‚ü©
      rcases h.2 with h2 | h2
      ¬∑ exact Or.inl h2
      ¬∑ exact Or.inr h2
    ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®h1, h2‚ü© hv
      rcases hv with hv | ‚ü®hvv, huu‚ü©
      ¬∑ exact absurd hv (by rw [h1]; decide)
      ¬∑ rcases h2 with h2 | h2
        ¬∑ exact absurd hvv (by rw [h2]; decide)
        ¬∑ exact absurd huu (by rw [h2]; decide)
  rw [this]
  exact (isClosed_coord_false (u, v)).inter
    ((isClosed_coord_true (v, v)).union (isClosed_coord_true (u, u)))

omit [CommRing A] in
/-- **Closedness of `vle_total` in Bool form.** -/
lemma isClosed_vle_total_bool :
    IsClosed {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | ‚ąÄ f s : A, vleOfBool r f s ‚ą® vleOfBool r s f} := by
  rw [show {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | ‚ąÄ f s : A, vleOfBool r f s ‚ą® vleOfBool r s f} =
      ‚čā (f : A), ‚čā (s : A), {r | vleOfBool r f s ‚ą® vleOfBool r s f} by
    ext r; simp]
  exact isClosed_iInter fun f => isClosed_iInter fun s =>
    (isClosed_vleOfBool f s).union (isClosed_vleOfBool s f)

omit [CommRing A] in
/-- **Closedness of `vle_trans` in Bool form.** A single universally quantified
implication `A ‚Üí B` is closed since `{r | A ‚Üí B} = {r | ¬¨A} ‚ą™ {r | B}`, and both
pieces are clopens in the Bool product. -/
lemma isClosed_vle_trans_bool :
    IsClosed {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool |
      ‚ąÄ x y z : A, vleOfBool r x y ‚Üí vleOfBool r y z ‚Üí vleOfBool r x z} := by
  rw [show {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool |
      ‚ąÄ x y z : A, vleOfBool r x y ‚Üí vleOfBool r y z ‚Üí vleOfBool r x z} =
      ‚čā (x : A), ‚čā (y : A), ‚čā (z : A),
        {r | vleOfBool r x y ‚Üí vleOfBool r y z ‚Üí vleOfBool r x z} by
    ext r; simp]
  refine isClosed_iInter fun x => isClosed_iInter fun y => isClosed_iInter fun z => ?_
  have rewriteEq :
      {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool |
        vleOfBool r x y ‚Üí vleOfBool r y z ‚Üí vleOfBool r x z} =
      {r | ¬¨ vleOfBool r x y} ‚ą™ {r | ¬¨ vleOfBool r y z} ‚ą™
        {r | vleOfBool r x z} := by
    ext r
    constructor
    ¬∑ intro h
      by_cases h1 : vleOfBool r x y
      ¬∑ by_cases h2 : vleOfBool r y z
        ¬∑ exact Or.inr (h h1 h2)
        ¬∑ exact Or.inl (Or.inr h2)
      ¬∑ exact Or.inl (Or.inl h1)
    ¬∑ rintro ((h1 | h2) | h3) hxy hyz
      ¬∑ exact absurd hxy h1
      ¬∑ exact absurd hyz h2
      ¬∑ exact h3
  rw [rewriteEq]
  exact ((isClosed_not_vleOfBool x y).union (isClosed_not_vleOfBool y z)).union
    (isClosed_vleOfBool x z)

/-- **Closedness of `vle_add` in Bool form.** -/
lemma isClosed_vle_add_bool :
    IsClosed {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool |
      ‚ąÄ x y z : A, vleOfBool r x z ‚Üí vleOfBool r y z ‚Üí vleOfBool r (x + y) z} := by
  rw [show {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool |
      ‚ąÄ x y z : A, vleOfBool r x z ‚Üí vleOfBool r y z ‚Üí vleOfBool r (x + y) z} =
      ‚čā (x : A), ‚čā (y : A), ‚čā (z : A),
        {r | vleOfBool r x z ‚Üí vleOfBool r y z ‚Üí vleOfBool r (x + y) z} by
    ext r; simp]
  refine isClosed_iInter fun x => isClosed_iInter fun y => isClosed_iInter fun z => ?_
  have rewriteEq :
      {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool |
        vleOfBool r x z ‚Üí vleOfBool r y z ‚Üí vleOfBool r (x + y) z} =
      {r | ¬¨ vleOfBool r x z} ‚ą™ {r | ¬¨ vleOfBool r y z} ‚ą™
        {r | vleOfBool r (x + y) z} := by
    ext r
    constructor
    ¬∑ intro h
      by_cases h1 : vleOfBool r x z
      ¬∑ by_cases h2 : vleOfBool r y z
        ¬∑ exact Or.inr (h h1 h2)
        ¬∑ exact Or.inl (Or.inr h2)
      ¬∑ exact Or.inl (Or.inl h1)
    ¬∑ rintro ((h1 | h2) | h3) hxz hyz
      ¬∑ exact absurd hxz h1
      ¬∑ exact absurd hyz h2
      ¬∑ exact h3
  rw [rewriteEq]
  exact ((isClosed_not_vleOfBool x z).union (isClosed_not_vleOfBool y z)).union
    (isClosed_vleOfBool (x + y) z)

/-- **Closedness of `mul_vle_mul_left` in Bool form.** -/
lemma isClosed_mul_vle_mul_left_bool :
    IsClosed {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool |
      ‚ąÄ x y : A, vleOfBool r x y ‚Üí ‚ąÄ z : A, vleOfBool r (x * z) (y * z)} := by
  rw [show {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool |
      ‚ąÄ x y : A, vleOfBool r x y ‚Üí ‚ąÄ z : A, vleOfBool r (x * z) (y * z)} =
      ‚čā (x : A), ‚čā (y : A), ‚čā (z : A),
        {r | vleOfBool r x y ‚Üí vleOfBool r (x * z) (y * z)} by
    ext r; constructor
    ¬∑ intro h; simp only [Set.mem_iInter, Set.mem_setOf_eq]
      intro x y z hxy; exact h x y hxy z
    ¬∑ intro h x y hxy z; simp only [Set.mem_iInter, Set.mem_setOf_eq] at h
      exact h x y z hxy]
  refine isClosed_iInter fun x => isClosed_iInter fun y => isClosed_iInter fun z => ?_
  have rewriteEq :
      {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool |
        vleOfBool r x y ‚Üí vleOfBool r (x * z) (y * z)} =
      {r | ¬¨ vleOfBool r x y} ‚ą™ {r | vleOfBool r (x * z) (y * z)} := by
    ext r
    constructor
    ¬∑ intro h
      by_cases h1 : vleOfBool r x y
      ¬∑ exact Or.inr (h h1)
      ¬∑ exact Or.inl h1
    ¬∑ rintro (h1 | h2) hxy
      ¬∑ exact absurd hxy h1
      ¬∑ exact h2
  rw [rewriteEq]
  exact (isClosed_not_vleOfBool x y).union (isClosed_vleOfBool (x * z) (y * z))

/-- **Closedness of `vle_mul_cancel` in Bool form.** -/
lemma isClosed_vle_mul_cancel_bool :
    IsClosed {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool |
      ‚ąÄ x y z : A, ¬¨ vleOfBool r z 0 ‚Üí vleOfBool r (x * z) (y * z) ‚Üí vleOfBool r x y} := by
  rw [show {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool |
      ‚ąÄ x y z : A, ¬¨ vleOfBool r z 0 ‚Üí vleOfBool r (x * z) (y * z) ‚Üí vleOfBool r x y} =
      ‚čā (x : A), ‚čā (y : A), ‚čā (z : A),
        {r | ¬¨ vleOfBool r z 0 ‚Üí vleOfBool r (x * z) (y * z) ‚Üí vleOfBool r x y} by
    ext r; simp]
  refine isClosed_iInter fun x => isClosed_iInter fun y => isClosed_iInter fun z => ?_
  have rewriteEq :
      {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool |
        ¬¨ vleOfBool r z 0 ‚Üí vleOfBool r (x * z) (y * z) ‚Üí vleOfBool r x y} =
      {r | vleOfBool r z 0} ‚ą™ {r | ¬¨ vleOfBool r (x * z) (y * z)} ‚ą™
        {r | vleOfBool r x y} := by
    ext r
    constructor
    ¬∑ intro h
      by_cases h1 : vleOfBool r z 0
      ¬∑ exact Or.inl (Or.inl h1)
      ¬∑ by_cases h2 : vleOfBool r (x * z) (y * z)
        ¬∑ exact Or.inr (h h1 h2)
        ¬∑ exact Or.inl (Or.inr h2)
    ¬∑ rintro ((h1 | h2) | h3) hz hxz
      ¬∑ exact absurd h1 hz
      ¬∑ exact absurd hxz h2
      ¬∑ exact h3
  rw [rewriteEq]
  exact ((isClosed_vleOfBool z 0).union (isClosed_not_vleOfBool (x * z) (y * z))).union
    (isClosed_vleOfBool x y)

/-- **Closedness of `not_vle_one_zero` in Bool form.** A single negated condition. -/
lemma isClosed_not_vle_one_zero_bool :
    IsClosed {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | ¬¨ vleOfBool r 1 0} := by
  have : {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | ¬¨ vleOfBool r 1 0} =
      {r | r (1, 0) = false} ‚ą©
        ({r | r (0, 0) = true} ‚ą™ {r | r (1, 1) = true}) := by
    ext r
    constructor
    ¬∑ intro h
      simp only [vleOfBool, not_or, not_and_or, Bool.not_eq_true, Bool.not_eq_false] at h
      refine ‚ü®h.1, ?_‚ü©
      rcases h.2 with h2 | h2
      ¬∑ exact Or.inl h2
      ¬∑ exact Or.inr h2
    ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®h1, h2‚ü© hv
      rcases hv with hv | ‚ü®hvv, huu‚ü©
      ¬∑ exact absurd hv (by rw [h1]; decide)
      ¬∑ rcases h2 with h2 | h2
        ¬∑ exact absurd hvv (by rw [h2]; decide)
        ¬∑ exact absurd huu (by rw [h2]; decide)
  rw [this]
  exact (isClosed_coord_false (1, 0)).inter
    ((isClosed_coord_true (0, 0)).union (isClosed_coord_true (1, 1)))

/-- **Closedness of `apply_iff` (consistency) in Bool form.** The condition is
`r (f,s) = true ‚ÜĒ vleOfBool r f s ‚ąß ¬¨ vleOfBool r s 0`. This is a finite Boolean
combination of coordinate conditions, hence closed. -/
lemma isClosed_apply_iff_bool :
    IsClosed {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool |
      ‚ąÄ f s : A, (r (f, s) = true) ‚ÜĒ vleOfBool r f s ‚ąß ¬¨ vleOfBool r s 0} := by
  rw [show {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool |
      ‚ąÄ f s : A, (r (f, s) = true) ‚ÜĒ vleOfBool r f s ‚ąß ¬¨ vleOfBool r s 0} =
      ‚čā (f : A), ‚čā (s : A),
        {r | (r (f, s) = true) ‚ÜĒ vleOfBool r f s ‚ąß ¬¨ vleOfBool r s 0} by
    ext r; simp]
  refine isClosed_iInter fun f => isClosed_iInter fun s => ?_
  -- `P ‚ÜĒ Q` = `(¬¨P ‚ą® Q) ‚ąß (P ‚ą® ¬¨Q)`.
  have rewriteEq :
      {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | (r (f, s) = true) ‚ÜĒ vleOfBool r f s ‚ąß ¬¨ vleOfBool r s 0} =
      ({r | r (f, s) = false} ‚ą™
        ({r | vleOfBool r f s} ‚ą© {r | ¬¨ vleOfBool r s 0})) ‚ą©
      ({r | r (f, s) = true} ‚ą™
        ({r | ¬¨ vleOfBool r f s} ‚ą™ {r | vleOfBool r s 0})) := by
    ext r
    constructor
    ¬∑ intro h
      refine ‚ü®?_, ?_‚ü©
      ¬∑ by_cases hrfs : r (f, s) = true
        ¬∑ exact Or.inr (h.mp hrfs)
        ¬∑ left; exact (Bool.not_eq_true _).mp hrfs
      ¬∑ by_cases hrhs : vleOfBool r f s ‚ąß ¬¨ vleOfBool r s 0
        ¬∑ exact Or.inl (h.mpr hrhs)
        ¬∑ right
          rw [not_and_or] at hrhs
          rcases hrhs with hrhs | hrhs
          ¬∑ exact Or.inl hrhs
          ¬∑ exact Or.inr (not_not.mp hrhs)
    ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®h1, h2‚ü©
      constructor
      ¬∑ intro hrfs
        rcases h1 with h1 | h1
        ¬∑ rw [h1] at hrfs; exact absurd hrfs (by decide)
        ¬∑ exact h1
      ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®hlhs1, hlhs2‚ü©
        rcases h2 with h2 | h2
        ¬∑ exact h2
        ¬∑ rcases h2 with h2 | h2
          ¬∑ exact absurd hlhs1 h2
          ¬∑ exact absurd h2 hlhs2
  rw [rewriteEq]
  refine IsClosed.inter ?_ ?_
  ¬∑ exact (isClosed_coord_false (f, s)).union
      ((isClosed_vleOfBool f s).inter (isClosed_not_vleOfBool s 0))
  ¬∑ exact (isClosed_coord_true (f, s)).union
      ((isClosed_not_vleOfBool f s).union (isClosed_vleOfBool s 0))

/-! #### Combined closedness of `IsValuationCharBool` -/

/-- Unfolded description of `IsValuationCharBool` as the conjunction of seven
universally quantified conditions, each a closed set in the discrete product. -/
lemma isValuationCharBool_iff (r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool) :
    IsValuationCharBool r ‚ÜĒ
      (‚ąÄ f s : A, vleOfBool r f s ‚ą® vleOfBool r s f) ‚ąß
      (‚ąÄ x y z : A, vleOfBool r x y ‚Üí vleOfBool r y z ‚Üí vleOfBool r x z) ‚ąß
      (‚ąÄ x y z : A, vleOfBool r x z ‚Üí vleOfBool r y z ‚Üí vleOfBool r (x + y) z) ‚ąß
      (‚ąÄ x y : A, vleOfBool r x y ‚Üí ‚ąÄ z : A, vleOfBool r (x * z) (y * z)) ‚ąß
      (‚ąÄ x y z : A, ¬¨ vleOfBool r z 0 ‚Üí vleOfBool r (x * z) (y * z) ‚Üí vleOfBool r x y) ‚ąß
      (¬¨ vleOfBool r 1 0) ‚ąß
      (‚ąÄ f s : A, (r (f, s) = true) ‚ÜĒ vleOfBool r f s ‚ąß ¬¨ vleOfBool r s 0) := by
  simp only [IsValuationCharBool, vleOfBool_iff_vleOf_decide]
  refine ‚ü®fun hr => ?_, fun hr => ?_‚ü©
  ¬∑ refine ‚ü®hr.vle_total, @hr.vle_trans, @hr.vle_add, @hr.mul_vle_mul_left,
      @hr.vle_mul_cancel, hr.not_vle_one_zero, ?_‚ü©
    intro f s
    have := hr.apply_iff f s
    -- This unfolds vleOf (fun p => r p = true) f s ‚ÄĒ already matches.
    exact this
  ¬∑ obtain ‚ü®h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6, h7‚ü© := hr
    exact {
      vle_total := h1
      vle_trans := @h2
      vle_add := @h3
      mul_vle_mul_left := @h4
      vle_mul_cancel := @h5
      not_vle_one_zero := h6
      apply_iff := h7
    }

/-- The set of Bool valuation characteristics is closed in the discrete product. -/
lemma isClosed_isValuationCharBool :
    IsClosed {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | IsValuationCharBool r} := by
  -- Unfold IsValuationCharBool to a conjunction of the seven axioms, each closed.
  have hEq : {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | IsValuationCharBool r} =
      {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | ‚ąÄ f s : A, vleOfBool r f s ‚ą® vleOfBool r s f} ‚ą©
      {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool |
        ‚ąÄ x y z : A, vleOfBool r x y ‚Üí vleOfBool r y z ‚Üí vleOfBool r x z} ‚ą©
      {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool |
        ‚ąÄ x y z : A, vleOfBool r x z ‚Üí vleOfBool r y z ‚Üí vleOfBool r (x + y) z} ‚ą©
      {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool |
        ‚ąÄ x y : A, vleOfBool r x y ‚Üí ‚ąÄ z : A, vleOfBool r (x * z) (y * z)} ‚ą©
      {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool |
        ‚ąÄ x y z : A, ¬¨ vleOfBool r z 0 ‚Üí vleOfBool r (x * z) (y * z) ‚Üí vleOfBool r x y} ‚ą©
      {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool | ¬¨ vleOfBool r 1 0} ‚ą©
      {r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool |
        ‚ąÄ f s : A, (r (f, s) = true) ‚ÜĒ vleOfBool r f s ‚ąß ¬¨ vleOfBool r s 0} := by
    ext r
    simp only [Set.mem_setOf_eq, Set.mem_inter_iff]
    rw [isValuationCharBool_iff]
    tauto
  rw [hEq]
  exact ((((((isClosed_vle_total_bool.inter isClosed_vle_trans_bool).inter
    isClosed_vle_add_bool).inter isClosed_mul_vle_mul_left_bool).inter
    isClosed_vle_mul_cancel_bool).inter isClosed_not_vle_one_zero_bool).inter
    isClosed_apply_iff_bool)

/-! #### Range of `őĻSpv_bool` equals the set of Bool valuation characteristics -/

/-- **Main range identity (Bool version).** The image of `őĻSpv_bool` is exactly the
set of Bool valuation characteristics. -/
theorem range_őĻSpv_bool :
    Set.range (őĻSpv_bool : Spv A ‚Üí (A √ó A ‚Üí Bool)) = {r | IsValuationCharBool r} := by
  ext r
  constructor
  ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®v, rfl‚ü©
    -- őĻSpv_bool v is a Bool valuation characteristic: transport IsValuationChar via the
    -- factorisation őĻSpv v = fun p => őĻSpv_bool v p = true.
    change IsValuationCharBool (őĻSpv_bool v)
    change IsValuationChar (fun p => őĻSpv_bool v p = true)
    -- Convert őĻSpv v to `fun p => őĻSpv_bool v p = true` pointwise.
    have hconv : (fun p => őĻSpv_bool v p = true) = őĻSpv v := by
      funext p
      have := őĻSpv_eq_boolToProp_comp_őĻSpv_bool v
      rw [this]; rfl
    rw [hconv]
    exact őĻSpv_mem_isValuationChar v
  ¬∑ intro hr
    -- From IsValuationChar (fun p => r p = true), construct v = hr'.toSpv where
    -- hr' : IsValuationChar (fun p => r p = true). Then őĻSpv_bool v = r.
    have hr' : IsValuationChar (fun p => r p = true) := hr
    refine ‚ü®hr'.toSpv, ?_‚ü©
    -- Show őĻSpv_bool hr'.toSpv = r.
    have key : őĻSpv hr'.toSpv = fun p => r p = true := őĻSpv_toSpv hr'
    funext p
    show őĻSpv_bool hr'.toSpv p = r p
    simp only [őĻSpv_bool]
    have hőĻSpv_p : őĻSpv hr'.toSpv p = (hr'.toSpv.vle p.1 p.2 ‚ąß ¬¨ hr'.toSpv.vle p.2 0) := rfl
    by_cases hb : r p = true
    ¬∑ rw [hb]
      simp only [decide_eq_true_iff]
      rw [‚Üź hőĻSpv_p, key]; exact hb
    ¬∑ have hbf : r p = false := (Bool.not_eq_true _).mp hb
      rw [hbf]
      simp only [decide_eq_false_iff_not]
      rw [‚Üź hőĻSpv_p, key]; exact hb

/-- **Closedness of the range of `őĻSpv_bool`.** -/
theorem isClosed_range_őĻSpv_bool :
    IsClosed (Set.range (őĻSpv_bool : Spv A ‚Üí (A √ó A ‚Üí Bool))) := by
  rw [range_őĻSpv_bool]
  exact isClosed_isValuationCharBool

/-! ### Conclusion: `CompactSpace (Spv A)` -/

/-- `Set.range őĻSpv_bool` is compact (closed subset of the compact space
`A √ó A ‚Üí Bool`). -/
lemma isCompact_range_őĻSpv_bool :
    IsCompact (Set.range (őĻSpv_bool : Spv A ‚Üí (A √ó A ‚Üí Bool))) :=
  isClosed_range_őĻSpv_bool.isCompact

/-- `Set.range őĻSpv` equals the image of `range őĻSpv_bool` under the pointwise
`boolToProp` map. -/
lemma range_őĻSpv_eq_image_boolToProp :
    Set.range (őĻSpv : Spv A ‚Üí (A √ó A ‚Üí Prop)) =
      (fun r : A √ó A ‚Üí Bool => fun p => boolToProp (r p)) ''
        Set.range (őĻSpv_bool : Spv A ‚Üí (A √ó A ‚Üí Bool)) := by
  ext s
  constructor
  ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®v, rfl‚ü©
    refine ‚ü®őĻSpv_bool v, ‚ü®v, rfl‚ü©, ?_‚ü©
    change (fun p => boolToProp (őĻSpv_bool v p)) = _
    exact (őĻSpv_eq_boolToProp_comp_őĻSpv_bool v).symm
  ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®r, ‚ü®v, rfl‚ü©, rfl‚ü©
    refine ‚ü®v, ?_‚ü©
    change _ = (fun p => boolToProp (őĻSpv_bool v p))
    exact őĻSpv_eq_boolToProp_comp_őĻSpv_bool v

/-- `Set.range őĻSpv` is compact in the Sierpinski product topology: it is the
continuous image of the closed range `range őĻSpv_bool` in the discrete Bool
product. -/
lemma isCompact_range_őĻSpv :
    IsCompact (Set.range (őĻSpv : Spv A ‚Üí (A √ó A ‚Üí Prop))) := by
  rw [range_őĻSpv_eq_image_boolToProp]
  exact isCompact_range_őĻSpv_bool.image continuous_boolToProp_pi

/-- **Capstone theorem: compactness of the valuation spectrum (Wedhorn Thm 4.9;
Huber 1993, Lemma 2.1 / Thm 3.1).** The valuation spectrum `Spv A` of a
commutative ring `A` is compact.

Proof: the Bool-valued Huber embedding `őĻSpv_bool : Spv A ‚Üí (A √ó A ‚Üí Bool)` has
closed image (each of the seven `IsValuationChar` axioms is a closed cylinder
condition; their intersection is closed). `(A √ó A ‚Üí Bool)` is compact (Tychonoff +
`Finite Bool`), so `range őĻSpv_bool` is compact. The pointwise conversion map
`boolToProp : Bool ‚Üí Prop` is continuous, giving `IsCompact (range őĻSpv)`. By
`őĻSpv_isEmbedding.isCompact_iff Set.univ`, this transfers back to compactness of
`Spv A`. -/
instance instCompactSpace : CompactSpace (Spv A) := by
  rw [‚Üź isCompact_univ_iff]
  -- We need: IsCompact (univ : Set (Spv A)). Use őĻSpv_isEmbedding.isCompact_iff.
  rw [őĻSpv_isEmbedding.isCompact_iff, Set.image_univ]
  exact isCompact_range_őĻSpv

end ValuationSpectrum
